      "explanation": "Why would the surface of Titan light up with a blinding flash? The reason: a sunglint from liquid seas.  Saturn's moon Titan has numerous smooth lakes of methane that, when the angle is right, reflect sunlight as if they were mirrors.  Pictured here in false-color, the robotic Cassini spacecraft orbiting Saturn imaged the cloud-covered Titan last summer in different bands of cloud-piercing infrared light.  This specular reflec",
